<DOC><DOCNO> AP880409-0173 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-09-88 0613EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-DigestBriefs     04-09 0644</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Digest Briefs,0672</SECOND><BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An Israeli girl hiking in the West Bank withfriends was likely killed by a bullet fired from the rifle ofanother Jewish settler, not from a stone flung by an Arab aspreviously reported, Israeli media said.   The reports, citing an army probe, raised the possibility thatone of the two settlers guarding the hikers inadvertently shot15-year-old Tirza Porat during a clash with Arabs in the village ofBeita on Wednesday.   The army said it had not determined the exact cause of thegirl's death, which prompted calls for revenge from settlers andled the army to blow up 13 homes in Beita belonging to Arabsallegedly involved in the clash.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Back home after logging 16,000 miles in afailed effort to get Arabs and Israelis to agree to negotiations,Secretary of State George P. Shultz says he won't be deterred fromtrying again.   Their reluctance to sign on to a two-stage U.S. proposal fornegotiations, means one deadline has passed and another almostcertainly will go by the boards.   The first was Shultz's call for a reply by mid-March. Israel andJordan, the two key parties, did not turn him down. But they alsodid not agree to the talks.   The second deadline was mid-April, the target date for aninternational peace conference. That obviously will not happen,Shultz said Friday at his last stop in Amman, Jordan.</TEXT><DATELINE>BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Jimmy Swaggart and the nation's largestPentecostal denomination walked away from each other after thechurch said it was defrocking him for rejecting its punishment for``moral failure.''   Swaggart on Friday announced his resignation from the Assembliesof God shortly after the church said it was ousting him forrefusing to undergo a year's suspension from the pulpit and atleast two years of rehabilitation.   The punishment was ordered after Swaggart confessed publicly tounspecified sins. Though never proven but also never disputed, itwas widely reported that Swaggart had committed lewd acts with aNew Orleans prostitute.</TEXT><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Former White House political director LynNofziger expects his conviction and 90-day prison sentence forillegal lobbying to be reversed, saying the prosecutor made``mountains out of molehills'' and lied.   ``I am an honorable man,'' Nofziger told U.S. District JudgeThomas A. Flannery, who also fined him $30,000 on Friday. ``Likeother honorable people, I have gone through life making mistakes,doing stupid things. ... But I am not a criminal.''   He said independent counsel James C. McKay was ``not anhonorable man.''.   Nofziger, a longtime associate of President Reagan, shook handswith friends and kissed his wife and other family members after thesentence was pronounced.</TEXT><DATELINE>SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Reagan has turned out awinner in the tax-reform law he championed, making more money andpaying less tax last year than he did in 1986.   The White House on Friday released copies of federal tax returnfiled by Reagan and his wife, Nancy. It showed their tax liabilityfor 1987 was $86,638, or 25.1 percent of their $345,359 grossincome.   In 1986, their tax bill had been $92,460 on a total income of$336,640, or 27.5 percent.</TEXT><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A panhandler who used a dying 3-year-old girland her brother to win sympathy has been charged in her beatingdeath, and police appealed for further help from the passerby whotried to save her life.   Benito Sanches, 36, a ``crack'' cocaine addict who came toAmerica in the 1980 Cuban boat lift, was charged Friday withsecond-degree murder in the death of his girlfriend's daughter,Maya Figueroa, police said.   She was the second toddler in two weeks to die a violent deathat the city's biggest welfare hotel, The Prince George Hotel.</TEXT></DOC>